On Wednesday 25th of November 2020, Senator Elisha Abbo defected to the ruling All Progressives Congress (APC) from the opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP). Daily Times reports Senate President Ahmad Lawan read the Adamawa North lawmaker’s defection letter during Wednesday’s plenary session. READ ALSO: Umahi unhappy with PDP over Atiku’s choice of Peter Obi — Wike In the letter, Senator Abbo explained that Senator Elisha Abbo left the PDP because of the mismanagement of the party in Adamawa state by Governor Umaru Fintiri. This comes days after Dave Umahi, Ebonyi State governor, left PDP for APC. The governor alleged injustice being done by the PDP against the South-East as his reason for defection.